The paper discusses the training of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) using multiple discriminators, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the optimization of multiple objectives, which is a common problem in the field of optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of GANs. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of gradient descent and hypervolume maximization algorithms, which are common optimization techniques in the subfields of neural networks (cs.NE) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively.
